  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "28-30. Lo, &c.—in the simplicity of his heart (as is evident from the reply), conscious that the required surrender had been made, and generously taking in his brethren with him—\"we\"; not in the spirit of the young ruler. \"All these have I kept,\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "left all—\"The workmen's little is as much his \"all\" as the prince's much\" [Bengel]. In Matthew (Mt 19:27) he adds, \"What shall we have therefore?\" How shall it fare with us?",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
