  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then Peter said,.... \"To him\", as the Syriac and Arabic versions add; that is, to the Lord Jesus, as the Ethiopic version expresses it; who was always the most forward to speak on any occasion: he observing what was required of the young man, and how unwilling he was to comply with it, and the difficulty in every rich man's way of entrance into the kingdom of God, spoke as follows; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "lo, we have left all: the Arabic version reads, \"all ours\"; all we had, our friends, trades, and worldly substance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and followed thee: in Matthew 19:27 it is added, \"what shall we have therefore\"; referring to the promise of Christ, to the young man, that should he sell all he had, and give it to the poor, he should have treasure in heaven; See Gill on Matthew 19:27. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and followed thee: in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 19:27",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " it is added, \"what shall we have therefore\"; referring to the promise of Christ, to the young man, that should he sell all he had, and give it to the poor, he should have treasure in heaven; See Gill on ",
